1
00:00:01,040 --> 00:00:02,720
Remember...
牢記

2
00:00:04,160 --> 00:00:06,560
The date was April 12th.
那天是4月12日

3
00:00:06,640 --> 00:00:11,200
The space shuttle is about to be launched. Vostok 1.
航太飛機沃斯托克1號即將發射

4
00:00:11,280 --> 00:00:14,680
He used to launch shuttles, but still no one comes around.
他曾經發射過航太飛機，但仍然冇人來接他

5
00:00:16,040 --> 00:00:17,240
A STAR FELL FROM THE SKY
流行劃過夜空

6
00:00:18,520 --> 00:00:19,840
I MADE A WISH
我許下一個願望

7
00:00:22,440 --> 00:00:23,720
I WISHED THEY ALL DIED
我希望他們都死了

8
00:00:24,800 --> 00:00:26,160
Mom, I need to ask you something.
媽  我要問你一件事

9
00:00:26,240 --> 00:00:28,040
Why did you lie that day?
你那天為什麼說謊？

10
00:00:28,120 --> 00:00:31,160
You and Selim, when I asked you how that house burned down?
當我問你那所房子是怎麼被燒毀的時候  你和塞利姆為什麼說謊？

11
00:00:31,240 --> 00:00:33,000
Why would I lie?
我為什麼要撒謊？

12
00:00:34,200 --> 00:00:35,760
You're going to make a decision.
你要做出決定

13
00:00:37,440 --> 00:00:39,960
Will I see your face again?
我會再見到你嗎？

14
00:00:43,520 --> 00:00:46,440
It's Firuz! Don't shoot! I'm coming out!
是菲魯茲！別開槍！我要出來了！

15
00:00:47,640 --> 00:00:50,240
I was on night duty when a man came by.
我上夜班的時候一個男人來找我

16
00:00:50,960 --> 00:00:53,000
I remember everything he said to me.
我記得他對我說的一切

17
00:00:53,560 --> 00:00:57,080
"You will forget about this. Or you will disappear," he said.
他說：“你會忘記這些事，否則你會消失的  ”

18
00:00:57,680 --> 00:01:01,120
- Tell me you're letting me go. - Let's say I let you go.
-告訴我  你會放我走  -假設我放你走

19
00:01:02,720 --> 00:01:05,320
Will everything you've done all these years also let you go?
這些年來你所做的一切會放過你嗎？

20
00:01:05,920 --> 00:01:08,160
I asked you if you're mafia, son!
我問你是不是黑手黨！

21
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:09,920
Yeah. We are. So what?
是，那又怎樣？

22
00:01:10,480 --> 00:01:13,120
Good. Here's your mafia.
好，這就是黑手黨的下場

23
00:01:13,640 --> 00:01:17,880
PERSONAL
個人

24
00:01:20,360 --> 00:01:21,520
Bro...
兄弟

25
00:01:22,360 --> 00:01:24,160
This is an incredible idea, Deva.
德瓦，這真是一個不可思議的想法

26
00:01:25,040 --> 00:01:27,600
- You see it, right? - Yeah. I see it.
-看到了吧 -是的

27
00:01:27,680 --> 00:01:29,600
How many people have written in?
有多少人在這裏留言？

28
00:01:29,680 --> 00:01:32,400
It's as if they've waited their whole lives for this moment.
好像他們已經等了一輩子了

29
00:01:33,080 --> 00:01:35,320
Waiting for someone to ask them their opinion.
等待別人問他們的意見

30
00:01:35,400 --> 00:01:37,240
There are some great replies here.
這裏有一些很好的回複

31
00:01:37,320 --> 00:01:38,880
Here are some. Listen up.
聽著

32
00:01:39,440 --> 00:01:41,800
Whom would you like Dog Slayer to kill?
你想讓狗殺手殺死誰？

33
00:01:43,240 --> 00:01:46,080
He should kill the people who sit around on park benches,
他應該殺死坐在公園長椅上的人

34
00:01:46,160 --> 00:01:48,120
eating nuts and scattering trash everywhere.
吃著堅果  亂扔垃圾

35
00:01:55,400 --> 00:01:56,440
Here's another one.
還有這個

36
00:01:58,280 --> 00:02:01,800
Wouldn't it be great if he killed the ones who refuse to stop honking?
如果他殺死不停按喇叭的人，那不是很好嗎？

37
00:02:13,160 --> 00:02:14,480
It would be.
還真是不錯

38
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:16,560
Here's another one.
還有這個

39
00:02:16,640 --> 00:02:18,400
You know how when you're waiting in line
你是否覺得當你排隊的時候

40
00:02:18,960 --> 00:02:21,560
and the person behind you is standing too close to you?
你背後的人離你太近了嗎？

41
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,040
He should kill them so we can finally breathe.
他應該殺死他們，以便我們放鬆下來

42
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:40,360
Let me see.
讓我看看

43
00:02:42,800 --> 00:02:44,720
"Dear Dog Slayer..."
“親愛的狗殺手”

44
00:02:44,800 --> 00:02:46,880
My mom forbade me from going on the internet
“我媽媽禁止我上網”

45
00:02:47,520 --> 00:02:52,800
"because I'm doing bad at school. Could you please kill my mom?"
“因為我在學校學習不好，能請你殺死我媽媽嗎？”

46
00:02:53,520 --> 00:02:55,960
- So it says. - He wants him to kill his mom?
-上麵這樣寫的  -他要他殺死他的媽媽？

47
00:02:56,040 --> 00:03:00,080
It seems so. Look at his nickname.
看來是的，你看他的昵稱

48
00:03:00,680 --> 00:03:01,720
Vengeful generation.
複仇的一代

49
00:04:37,840 --> 00:04:40,080
So this Mehmet Yurtgil went to the doctor.
所以這位穆罕默德·尤特吉爾去找過醫生

50
00:04:40,760 --> 00:04:43,640
He threatened the doctor and shut him up by scaring him.
他威脅醫生並通過恐嚇使他閉嘴

51
00:04:44,800 --> 00:04:48,000
And then, he forces him to write this report about Ufuk.
然後，醫生被強迫撰寫有關烏福克的報告

52
00:04:48,080 --> 00:04:49,800
- Is that so? - Yes, sir.
-是嗎  -是的長官

53
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:53,800
And the first victim is this Mehmet Yurtgil.
並且第一位受害者就是穆罕默德·尤爾吉爾

54
00:04:56,960 --> 00:05:00,600
You remember when I told you that I'd picked you from among 50 women?
你還記得我告訴過我我是從50位女性中選出你的嗎？

55
00:05:01,200 --> 00:05:05,160
Thank you for not letting me down. I have another thing to thank you on.
謝謝你冇有讓我失望  我還有另一件事要感謝你

56
00:05:05,240 --> 00:05:07,440
The other day, when we were talking in my room
前幾天，當我們在我的房間裏聊天時

57
00:05:07,520 --> 00:05:11,280
and I told you that what's happening might have nothing to do with Kambura...
我告訴你發生的事情可能與坎佈拉無關

58
00:05:12,360 --> 00:05:16,040
You know how you asked me for the file? How you didn't give up on it?
你知道你是怎麼問我這個文件的嗎？你怎麼不放棄呢？

59
00:05:16,760 --> 00:05:18,280
Thank you for that, as well.
也謝謝你

60
00:05:19,400 --> 00:05:21,040
Good job. We're getting closer.
幹得好  我們越來越接近了

61
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:26,680
What did the good sir write this time?
好先生這次寫了什麼？

62
00:05:27,440 --> 00:05:30,200
They all had the same word written on them.
他們都是相同的字眼

63
00:05:30,280 --> 00:05:31,520
"Personal."
“個人”

64
00:05:32,480 --> 00:05:36,400
"Personal." So he killed them for his own reasons, huh?
“個人”  所以他是出於個人原因殺死了他們，是嗎？

65
00:05:37,160 --> 00:05:39,720
- Seems so. - Then...
-似乎如此  -那麼……

66
00:05:40,880 --> 00:05:43,200
Whom did he kill all these people for?  Who are they?
他為誰殺了這些人？他們是什麼人？

67
00:05:44,040 --> 00:05:47,600
Chief, these men had 80 priors. 
長官，這些人有80個前科

68
00:05:47,680 --> 00:05:51,800
Accessory. Forgery. Their rap sheet is something to behold.
同謀罪  僞造罪  這些人的前科值得一看

69
00:05:51,880 --> 00:05:55,240
But they're not connected to Kambura. No fingerprints, either.
但他們都與坎佈拉無關  也冇有找到任何指紋

70
00:05:55,320 --> 00:05:57,600
But the crime was caught on CCTV.
但犯罪過程被監控拍了下來

71
00:05:57,680 --> 00:05:59,880
Let me guess. Cat costume.
我猜一定是穿了貓服裝

72
00:06:01,600 --> 00:06:02,600
Yes.
是的

73
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:07,720
We were able to follow him a long while through neighborhood shops' cameras.
我們能夠通過附近商店的攝像機跟著他走了很長時間

74
00:06:08,880 --> 00:06:11,200
He went in and out of a few streets.
他進出幾條街

75
00:06:11,280 --> 00:06:14,320
He acted like he wasn't sure which way he was supposed to be headed.
他的舉動就像他不確定他應該去往哪個方嚮

76
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:18,960
He went into a construction site, because that whole area is a construction site
他進入一個建築工地，因為整個區域都是一個建築工地

77
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:22,360
and there are no cameras looking inside, we lost the suspect.
而且裏麵冇有攝像頭，所以我們跟丟了

78
00:06:23,160 --> 00:06:25,290
We lost him because of the urban transformation project.
由於城市改造項目  所以跟丟了

79
00:06:25,320 --> 00:06:26,720
He had his escape planned.
他有逃跑計畫

80
00:06:27,280 --> 00:06:31,040
Those construction sites are like black holes in the middle of our cities.
這些建築工地就像我們城市中心的黑洞

81
00:06:33,600 --> 00:06:35,520
This is bad. This is really bad.
這很糟糕  這真的很糟糕

82
00:06:35,600 --> 00:06:38,640
This is really bad. Everyone's getting on the ride.
這真的很糟糕  每個人都在搭順風車

83
00:06:38,720 --> 00:06:42,760
Whoever has a bone to pick will shoot, kill, and blame him!
誰有骨氣，誰就開槍，誰就殺人，誰就嫁禍於他!

84
00:06:45,560 --> 00:06:47,720
So we have the Kambura connection.
那麼我們怎麼與坎佈拉聯係起來

85
00:06:48,200 --> 00:06:49,480
What do you think?
你怎麼看？

86
00:06:50,040 --> 00:06:52,680
Tayyar Kaymak, who died in the house that night,
塔亞爾·凱馬克，那天晚上被燒死在房子裏的人

87
00:06:52,760 --> 00:06:54,120
has a brother, Hamza Kaymak.
他有一個兄弟叫做哈姆薩·凱馬克

88
00:06:54,680 --> 00:06:56,320
We think he might know something.
我們認為他可能知道一些事

89
00:06:56,400 --> 00:07:00,200
Maybe he's the killer. Maybe he wants to avenge his brother.
也許他是殺手  也許他想為他兄弟報仇

90
00:07:00,760 --> 00:07:01,760
No, sir.
不，長官

91
00:07:01,840 --> 00:07:05,400
He was in prison for mugging someone while the murders were being committed.
在兇手殺人期間他因搶劫而入獄

92
00:07:06,200 --> 00:07:08,480
He's in prison, huh? Fine. Alright.
他在監獄裏嗎？好吧

93
00:07:08,960 --> 00:07:12,000
But he has to know something. He's Tayyar's brother after all, right?
但是他一定知道什麼事情  畢竟他是塔亞爾的兄弟，不是嗎？

94
00:07:12,080 --> 00:07:15,640
We need to find out what he knows. Go to his prison and talk to him.
我們需要搞清楚他知道些什麼  去監獄和他談談

95
00:07:17,160 --> 00:07:18,280
He escaped.
他越獄了

96
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:23,760
He fled the night when we were trying to get Ufuk out of Kambura.
當我們試圖將烏福克從坎佈拉開出來的時候

97
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,360
There's a manhunt for him right now.
現在有人在追捕他

98
00:07:25,440 --> 00:07:26,720
No way...
不可能……

99
00:07:28,680 --> 00:07:30,760
See, Sefa? Another escape.
看，塞法？又一次越獄

100
00:07:30,840 --> 00:07:34,440
Come on, Chief. It was a lapse of judgement.
別這樣長官   那是一次錯誤的判斷

101
00:07:34,520 --> 00:07:37,040
He handed himself in. How could I've known he'd try that?
他是自首的，我怎麼可能預料到他會逃跑？

102
00:07:37,120 --> 00:07:39,360
Anyway. Fine. Here's what we're going to do.
好吧  總之  我們接下來這樣做

103
00:07:39,440 --> 00:07:42,600
Nevra, you go after Tayyar's brother.
內芙拉，你去追捕塔亞爾的兄弟

104
00:07:42,680 --> 00:07:45,600
Get print-outs of his mugshot. Spread them around.
把他的照片列印出來  分發出去

105
00:07:45,680 --> 00:07:48,160
If he's out there, someone will have seen him.
如果他在外麵，有人會看到他的

106
00:07:48,800 --> 00:07:52,280
Sefa, you gather more information on the house that burned down.
塞法，你去收集有關被燒毀房屋的更多信息

107
00:07:52,360 --> 00:07:55,040
Anyone who remembers or knows something about that night...
任何記得或知道那晚事情的人

108
00:07:55,600 --> 00:07:57,880
Get the whole Kambura in here for interrogation.
把坎佈拉的所有人都詢問一遍

109
00:07:57,960 --> 00:07:59,840
- Let's go. - Right away, Chief.
-行動  -是的  長官

110
00:08:29,920 --> 00:08:31,400
This is not going to work out.
這樣不行的

111
00:08:32,000 --> 00:08:35,200
What if I get really sick before I do all these people in?
如果我在殺掉所有人之前就病的不行了怎麼辦？

112
00:08:38,680 --> 00:08:40,200
Then...
然後

113
00:08:41,800 --> 00:08:43,400
First...
首先

114
00:08:52,440 --> 00:08:53,840
Hello.
你好

115
00:08:55,840 --> 00:08:57,400
Do you have a last wish?
你有遺願嗎？

116
00:08:58,480 --> 00:08:59,920
No?
冇有？

117
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,240
You do?
你有？

118
00:09:03,240 --> 00:09:04,800
Forgive me, but I don't give a toss.
原諒我，但我不在乎

119
00:09:15,200 --> 00:09:16,440
Hello?
你好？

120
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:19,600
Yes?
是？

121
00:09:21,680 --> 00:09:22,680
Who?
誰？

122
00:09:27,520 --> 00:09:28,720
Who, did you say?
你說誰？

123
00:09:32,600 --> 00:09:36,280
- Hamza Kaymak, right? - Yes, Ates, it's really urgent.
-哈姆薩·凱馬克，對嗎？-是的，阿提斯，這真的很緊急

124
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:41,000
Don't worry. His photos will be everywhere in half an hour.
別擔心，半小時之內到處都是他的照片

125
00:09:42,560 --> 00:09:43,720
Thank you.
謝謝

126
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:47,280
When will I see you?
我什麼時候能見到你？

127
00:09:48,560 --> 00:09:50,520
I don't know when I'll be able to get out of here.
我不知道我什麼時候可以離開這裏

128
00:09:50,600 --> 00:09:52,280
Do you go home at all?
你有回過家嗎？

129
00:09:53,520 --> 00:09:56,560
- Sometimes, yes. - Can I come?
-有時候回去，是的  -我能去嗎？

130
00:10:00,720 --> 00:10:01,920
Come.
來吧

131
00:10:03,400 --> 00:10:04,400
Alright.
好的

132
00:10:36,160 --> 00:10:37,760
- Firuz... - Yeah?
-菲魯茲  -什麼事？

133
00:10:37,840 --> 00:10:39,240
What do you have?
你有什麼？

134
00:10:39,320 --> 00:10:41,000
Firuz, this won't get me in trouble, right?
菲魯茲，這不會給我帶來麻煩吧？

135
00:10:41,600 --> 00:10:45,000
Come on, Fiko! You've known me for years.
得了吧  菲科！你認識我多少年了

136
00:10:45,080 --> 00:10:46,480
Relax. You'll be fine.
放鬆  你會冇事的

137
00:10:46,560 --> 00:10:47,960
What is this? What did you find?
這是什麼？你找到了什麼？

138
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:51,400
I found some blood on the crime scene that doesn't belong to the victims.
我在犯罪現場發現了一些不屬於受害者的鮮血

139
00:10:51,480 --> 00:10:52,800
Probably belongs to the suspect.
可能屬於嫌疑犯

140
00:10:52,880 --> 00:10:54,720
- Is this the DNA report on it? - Yes.
-這是DNA報告嗎？  -是的

141
00:10:56,040 --> 00:10:57,160
Good.
好

142
00:10:58,880 --> 00:11:00,040
Here.
給你

143
00:11:02,120 --> 00:11:03,520
Don't spend it all in one place.
不要把所有的錢都花在一個地方

144
00:11:06,480 --> 00:11:09,400
This isn't in the file you provided the others, right?
這不在你提供給其他人的文件中，對嗎？

145
00:11:09,480 --> 00:11:11,640
- You threw it out, right? - Yes. I did.
-你把這些挑出來了？  -是的

146
00:11:12,480 --> 00:11:14,840
- I'll see you around. - Firuz. How's your boy doing?
-回見  -菲魯茲你兒子怎麼樣？

147
00:11:17,480 --> 00:11:19,640
The same. No change.
老樣子

148
00:11:37,720 --> 00:11:38,720
What's this?
這是什麼？

149
00:11:39,640 --> 00:11:41,560
Deva, take a look at this. Come here.
德瓦，過來看看這個

150
00:11:54,520 --> 00:11:56,720
Isn't that the corpse that was found in the jungle?
那不是在叢林中發現的屍體嗎？

151
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:58,280
Salim or something?
薩利姆還是誰？

152
00:11:59,800 --> 00:12:01,600
But what are they doing there?
但是他們在那裏做什麼？

153
00:12:03,040 --> 00:12:04,080
Who are they?
他們是什麼人？

154
00:12:05,040 --> 00:12:08,760
I don't know. Respond to them and let's get acquainted.
我不知道  回複他們  認識一下

155
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:44,040
One second. One second, miss.
等等，小姐

156
00:12:44,120 --> 00:12:45,760
Calm down for one second.
冷靜一下

157
00:12:45,840 --> 00:12:48,480
You saw the man from the photos, right?
你看到了照片中那個人，對不對？

158
00:12:48,960 --> 00:12:49,880
Alright.
好的

159
00:12:49,960 --> 00:12:51,320
Where did you see him?
你在哪裏看到他的？

160
00:12:53,760 --> 00:12:55,080
In a dream?
在夢中？

161
00:12:56,280 --> 00:12:57,840
You saw him in a dream.
你在夢中看到他

162
00:12:58,480 --> 00:12:59,920
Sweet dreams, miss.
祝你好夢，小姐

163
00:13:01,080 --> 00:13:05,040
- This is impossible. - Be patient. Something might turn up.
-真不可思議  -耐心一點  可能會有好事發生

164
00:13:05,600 --> 00:13:07,000
What are you doing?
你在做什麼？

165
00:13:07,080 --> 00:13:12,240
I'm making a list of the Kamburan gentry.
我正在列出坎佈拉人的名單

166
00:13:12,320 --> 00:13:15,200
Tomorrow is the Kambura Day at the station.
明天去坎佈拉

167
00:13:15,280 --> 00:13:17,640
I might tell them I'm their new leader.
我可能會告訴他們我是他們的新領導人

168
00:13:21,040 --> 00:13:22,800
Hello? Connect them.
餵？接進來

169
00:13:23,320 --> 00:13:27,880
Nevra, I'm calling your mom's husband in, as well.
內芙拉，我也會叫你媽媽的丈夫

170
00:13:30,640 --> 00:13:32,040
I'm listening, sir.
先生，我在聽

171
00:13:32,760 --> 00:13:34,160
Where did you see him?
你在哪裏看到他的？

172
00:13:35,000 --> 00:13:36,000
When?
什麼時候？

173
00:13:37,200 --> 00:13:38,960
Please stop wasting my time.
請不要浪費我的時間

174
00:13:53,960 --> 00:13:55,000
Ayhan?
艾漢

175
00:13:56,080 --> 00:13:58,680
- Ayhan, good luck with all this. - Thanks, Agah.
-艾漢，祝你一切順利  -謝謝，阿加

176
00:13:59,240 --> 00:14:01,440
We're doing our best to tidy up.
我們正在盡力整理

177
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:02,600
I'm sorry about last night.
昨晚我很抱歉

178
00:14:02,640 --> 00:14:05,960
You join us once in a blue moon, I wish it hadn't been so unpleasant.
你難得參加我們的活動，但願並冇有那麼令人不愉快

179
00:14:06,040 --> 00:14:09,120
It wasn't unpleasant. It was a proper disaster.
冇有不愉快  這是一場真正的災難

180
00:14:09,200 --> 00:14:12,120
What was that? I'm so glad we up and left.
那是什麼？我很高興我們起身離開了

181
00:14:12,200 --> 00:14:16,840
I wouldn't want to get beat up. I had a lady friend with me, too.
我也不想被打  我還有一個女伴和我一起

182
00:14:17,440 --> 00:14:19,680
We were so scared.
我們好害怕

183
00:14:19,760 --> 00:14:22,120
What business do you have with such men?
你和這些男人有什麼關係？

184
00:14:22,200 --> 00:14:25,000
Don't worry, Agah. There's nothing left to be scared of.
別擔心，阿加冇有什麼可害怕的

185
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,920
What do you mean? What if they come back?
你是什??麼意思，如果他們回來了怎麼辦？

186
00:14:27,000 --> 00:14:29,840
They were shot that night. All three are dead.
他們當晚被槍殺了  三個人都死了

187
00:14:30,480 --> 00:14:31,520
No way!
不是吧！

188
00:14:31,600 --> 00:14:34,320
Really. Not everyone's like us, after all.
畢竟，不是每個人都像我們一樣

189
00:14:34,400 --> 00:14:36,840
They must've gone after the wrong types.
他們一定是找了錯誤的目標

190
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:39,480
Tried to extort him, and got shot.
試圖勒索他，反被槍殺

191
00:14:40,240 --> 00:14:42,760
Istanbul has become unrecognizable.
伊斯坦佈爾變得麵目全非

192
00:14:42,840 --> 00:14:44,640
It shouldn't be this easy to kill people.
殺人不應該那麼容易

193
00:14:44,720 --> 00:14:46,880
Look how relaxed you are, talking about it.
看看你有多輕鬆的談論這件事

194
00:14:46,960 --> 00:14:50,800
I don't recognize Istanbul anymore. Especially not Beyoglu.
我已經不認識伊斯坦佈爾了，尤其是貝尤魯

195
00:14:50,880 --> 00:14:54,360
Oh, that old Beyoglu... That dear old Beyoglu...
哦，那個老貝尤魯  那個親愛的老貝尤魯

196
00:14:56,040 --> 00:14:58,480
What can I say? When you're right, you're right.
我能說什麼？如果你是對的，你就是對的

197
00:14:58,560 --> 00:15:00,200
Sadly, we've been getting reports
可悲的是，我們收到很多報告

198
00:15:00,280 --> 00:15:03,480
of mistreatment of residents from nursing homes more and more lately.
療養院對住戶的虐待最近越來越多

199
00:15:03,560 --> 00:15:06,720
However, we're at a stellar nursing home right now.
但是，我們現在是一家一流的養老院

200
00:15:06,800 --> 00:15:10,320
We have a resident with us. Let's ask her some questions.
這有一位住戶  讓我們問她一些問題

201
00:15:10,960 --> 00:15:15,280
Are you happy here? Would you like to say anything?
你在這裏開心嗎？你想說什麼嗎？

202
00:15:16,680 --> 00:15:18,400
I turned 65.
我65歲了

203
00:15:19,000 --> 00:15:21,440
You look great. I hope you see many more years yet.
你看起來很棒  我希望你能長命百歲

204
00:15:22,680 --> 00:15:25,840
On my last birthday, I made another wish.
在上一個生日，我又許了一個願望

205
00:15:27,560 --> 00:15:29,680
- Like a child. - That's great.
-像個孩子一樣  -太好了

206
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,840
It was another impossible wish, of course.
當然，這是另一個不可能的願望

207
00:15:34,600 --> 00:15:36,560
It might not be. I hope it comes true.
也許是不可能的，但我希望成真

208
00:15:37,560 --> 00:15:39,720
You know what I wished for?
你知道我想要什麼嗎？

209
00:15:41,320 --> 00:15:43,040
To become a good person.
成為一個好人

210
00:15:45,040 --> 00:15:48,560
- Great. We should all aspire to that. - She remembers everything.
-太好了，我們都應該朝這個方嚮努力  -她記得一切

211
00:15:49,160 --> 00:15:51,440
What is it, Agah? You're awfully interested in her.
阿加  你到底對她有什麼興趣

212
00:15:51,520 --> 00:15:54,360
No. I'm more interested in the TV.
不，我對電視更感興趣

213
00:15:54,960 --> 00:15:59,200
Mine's getting old. I might get one of these.
我老了  我可能會買一臺

214
00:16:00,640 --> 00:16:03,320
Do you like it here? How long have you been here?
你喜歡這裏嗎？你來這裏多久了？

215
00:16:04,960 --> 00:16:06,280
It's crystal clear.
水晶般清澈

216
00:16:07,200 --> 00:16:09,480
Whenever I come here,
每當我來這裏

217
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:12,320
something's on the TV.
電視上都有節目

218
00:16:13,760 --> 00:16:18,240
- Anyway... Good luck to you. - Thanks. Take care of yourself.
-反正祝你好運  -謝謝  照顧好自己

219
00:16:18,320 --> 00:16:22,000
Come on. Tidy it up. We're about to open back up.
整理一下，我們要重新開張了

220
00:16:24,040 --> 00:16:27,400
Come on. We need to tidy the place up. Customers are on the way.
來吧，我們需要整理一下  客人就快來了

221
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:31,840
So with Alzheimer's, let's say it's at an advanced stage.
對於老年癡呆癥患者，如果處於晚期

222
00:16:31,920 --> 00:16:35,280
It's all over. The patient remembers nothing.
一切都結束了  病人什麼都不記得

223
00:16:35,360 --> 00:16:37,760
Completely disconnected from the world.
完全脫離世界

224
00:16:37,840 --> 00:16:41,960
- Yes? - Might they suddenly remember?
-嗯？-他們會突然想起來嗎？

225
00:16:42,040 --> 00:16:43,960
Might they get their memory back?
他們會恢複記憶嗎？

226
00:16:44,040 --> 00:16:46,920
Is that possible? Is that a possibility? Does that happen?
那有可能嗎？有可能發生嗎？

227
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:51,320
Why are you asking me this? You're not at that stage yet.
你為什麼要問我這個？你還冇到那個階段

228
00:16:51,920 --> 00:16:54,120
It's too early to be worrying about stuff like this.
現在擔心這樣的事情還為時過早

229
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,840
I'm pondering every eventuality.
我正在考慮所有的可能

230
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:57,650
It's worth hoping for. Is it possible at all?
值得期待，那有可能嗎？

231
00:16:57,680 --> 00:17:00,880
I realize that I'll forget everything some day.
我意識到有一天我會忘記一切

232
00:17:00,960 --> 00:17:04,200
But I'm asking you if this is a possibility.
但是我問你這是否有可能

233
00:17:04,280 --> 00:17:05,600
Agah!
阿加！

234
00:17:06,200 --> 00:17:07,480
Alzheimer's...
老年癡呆癥

235
00:17:08,320 --> 00:17:10,960
Is still shrouded in mystery.
仍然籠罩在神秘之中

236
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,200
Each person is an exception.
每個人都是例外

237
00:17:13,280 --> 00:17:15,560
Each case progresses differently.
每個病人的發展情況都不一樣

238
00:17:16,120 --> 00:17:19,080
But in general, that's outside the realm of possibility.
但總的來說，幾乎不可能

239
00:17:19,800 --> 00:17:22,760
Possibilities, exceptions. You're not saying anything!
可能性，例外情況呢？  你什麼也冇說！

240
00:17:22,840 --> 00:17:25,000
I'm asking you if it's possible or not!
我問你是否可能！

241
00:17:25,080 --> 00:17:28,440
Remember when I told you about sudden bursts of anger?
還記得我告訴過你關於突然爆發的憤怒嗎？

242
00:17:28,520 --> 00:17:31,080
I don't want to talk about my bursts! Answer me!
我不想談論我的憤怒！回答我！

243
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:33,720
You're having one of those bursts right now.
你現在正遇到這些突發事件中的一種情況

244
00:17:33,800 --> 00:17:35,160
Because you don't answer!
因為你不回答！

245
00:17:35,240 --> 00:17:37,400
Because your question doesn't have an answer!
因為你的問題冇有答案！

246
00:17:42,280 --> 00:17:43,760
Forgive me.
原諒我

247
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:44,840
I mean...
我的意思是

248
00:17:45,440 --> 00:17:47,960
Even if there are no known cases...
即使冇有已知病例

249
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,160
It's possible.
但這是有可能的

250
00:17:51,400 --> 00:17:52,680
How about you relax now?
你現在放鬆一下怎麼樣？

251
00:17:52,760 --> 00:17:56,560
Take a few deep breaths through the nose. Relax...
深呼吸  放鬆一下……

252
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:59,200
I can relax later! I can't relax now! I have work to do!
我以後可以放鬆！我現在不能放鬆！我還有工作要做！

253
00:17:59,280 --> 00:18:01,760
- I'm leaving, with your permission. - Agah...
-我要離開，如果你允許的話  -阿加

254
00:18:02,520 --> 00:18:03,520
Yes?
是？

255
00:18:03,560 --> 00:18:07,680
- Are you up to something? - I don't... What do you mean?
-你在忙什麼？-我不是……什麼意思？

256
00:18:07,760 --> 00:18:09,760
Have you stopped taking your medication?
你已經停止服藥了嗎？

257
00:18:09,840 --> 00:18:12,280
Of course not. I'm taking my meds.
當然不是  我正在服用藥物

258
00:18:12,360 --> 00:18:14,120
- Are you sure? - Yes.
-確定嗎-是的

259
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:17,840
Alright. For your next appointment, please bring Zuhal along.
好吧，下次預約時，請帶上祖哈爾

260
00:18:17,920 --> 00:18:19,160
Excuse me? Why?
不好意思？為什麼？

261
00:18:19,240 --> 00:18:22,560
Is Zuhal the patient or am I? Why does she need to be here?
祖哈爾是患者還是我是患者？她為什麼需要在這裏？

262
00:18:25,360 --> 00:18:26,440
Alright, fine.
好  好

263
00:18:27,160 --> 00:18:29,040
Fine. I'll bring my daughter along.
好  我帶女兒來

264
00:18:52,720 --> 00:18:54,280
How will I get in?
我怎麼進去？

265
00:18:56,280 --> 00:18:58,000
Where will I get in?
從哪裏進去？

266
00:19:05,320 --> 00:19:07,320
You poor Agah.
可憐的阿加

267
00:19:08,040 --> 00:19:09,280
How will you...
你怎樣……

268
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:13,760
Of course you can't.
當然不能

269
00:19:15,400 --> 00:19:16,600
Of course you can't.
當然不能

270
00:19:17,160 --> 00:19:19,560
Serves you right for coming so unprepared.
你真是活該，冇做準備就來了

271
00:19:19,640 --> 00:19:23,360
You're not about to sprout wings and jump over the fence, are you?
你不會長出翅膀來跳過圍牆  對吧？

272
00:19:53,760 --> 00:19:56,160
Hello again.
再次問好

273
00:19:56,760 --> 00:20:00,920
You told me to come see you if I needed anything.
你告訴我如果有需要時就找你

274
00:20:01,800 --> 00:20:03,800
No matter what, you said.
不管需要什麼

275
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,160
I need something.
我需要個東西

276
00:20:07,960 --> 00:20:10,720
Could you please die for me?
你願意為我去死嗎？

277
00:20:35,240 --> 00:20:36,360
What are these?
這些是什麼？

278
00:20:37,920 --> 00:20:39,880
The best picnics...
最好的野餐

279
00:20:39,960 --> 00:20:41,720
Are those had at home, Nevra.
都是在家裏吃的

280
00:20:43,680 --> 00:20:46,520
I'll take that. Come in.
我拿進來

281
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,480
- Any news on Tayyar's brother? - No.
-有關於塔亞爾兄弟的消息嗎？-冇有

282
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:58,320
There are, actually. Some woman called.
其實有幾個女人打電話來

283
00:20:58,400 --> 00:21:00,520
Told me she saw him in her dreams.
告訴我她在夢中看到他

284
00:21:00,600 --> 00:21:03,280
- How does that sound? - Sounds great.
-聽起來怎麼樣？-聽起來很棒

285
00:21:05,040 --> 00:21:06,720
It's better than nothing.
總比冇有好

286
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,960
When did you move in here?
你什麼時候搬來的？

287
00:21:13,120 --> 00:21:15,720
As you can see, I never really did.
如你所見，我還冇真正搬進來

288
00:21:15,800 --> 00:21:17,720
It's been like this for like six months.
像這樣六個月了

289
00:21:19,720 --> 00:21:21,080
I think it looks nice.
我覺得很好看

290
00:21:21,680 --> 00:21:23,720
Maybe I should decorate my place after yours.
也許我應該用你的房間來裝飾我的房間

291
00:21:23,800 --> 00:21:27,560
I think that's a great idea. Everything's all tidied up, you see?
我認為這是個好主意，一切都整理好了，你知道嗎？

292
00:21:27,640 --> 00:21:31,360
Plus, when you want to move out, you don't have to do any packing up.
另外，當你要搬走的時候都不需要打包

293
00:21:33,160 --> 00:21:35,400
Why? Are you planning to go somewhere?
為什麼？你打算去某個地方嗎？

294
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:39,080
I always go somewhere, Ates.
我總是去某個地方，阿提斯

295
00:21:39,760 --> 00:21:43,520
You can't tell from the outside, but I very often leave my body.
你看不出來，但我經常離開我的身體

296
00:21:49,680 --> 00:21:52,360
- It's your turn. - What turn?
-輪到你了-輪到什麼了？

297
00:21:54,920 --> 00:21:56,680
I've told you everything about me.
我已經告訴過你關於我的一切

298
00:21:58,240 --> 00:22:00,560
Told you I've been rotting for years.
告訴你我已經腐爛多年了

299
00:22:02,360 --> 00:22:06,040
That all I want is to become that old Ates again.
我想要的就是再次成為那個以前的阿提斯

300
00:22:06,680 --> 00:22:08,240
That Ates who just got out of college.
那個剛從大學畢業的阿提斯

301
00:22:08,320 --> 00:22:11,600
That Ates who still believes in journalism.
仍然相信新聞的阿提斯

302
00:22:13,040 --> 00:22:16,320
I've shown you all my scars. Let you see all my pain.
我已經給你看了我所有的傷疤  讓你看到了我所有的痛苦

303
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:19,040
It's your turn to tell me.
該你告訴我了

304
00:22:21,120 --> 00:22:25,280
First, tell me why you knocked on my door that night.
首先，告訴我那天晚上你為什麼來我家

305
00:22:51,080 --> 00:22:52,240
You know how you say...
你知道當你說……

306
00:22:53,800 --> 00:22:56,840
That all you want is to become that old Ates again...
你想要的就是再次成為那個以前的阿提斯

307
00:22:58,320 --> 00:23:00,240
I'm the exact opposite.
我正好相反

308
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:04,240
What I fear most is becoming the old Nevra.
我最擔心的是成為以前的內芙拉

309
00:23:04,880 --> 00:23:06,040
Why?
為什麼？

310
00:23:07,200 --> 00:23:08,600
I think...
我認為……

311
00:23:09,600 --> 00:23:13,960
I don't know how to co-exist with people.
我不知道如何與人共存

312
00:23:15,480 --> 00:23:17,600
How to talk to people.
如何與人交談

313
00:23:18,240 --> 00:23:20,400
What to do with friends.
與朋友做什麼

314
00:23:21,280 --> 00:23:24,080
How to spend time with a boyfriend.
如何與男友共度時光

315
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:27,960
How to manage the space between you and someone else.
如何管理你與他人之間的空間

316
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:31,680
I don't know how to do any of that.
我不知道該怎麼做

317
00:23:31,760 --> 00:23:33,480
But I've always pretended to know.
但是我一直假裝知道

318
00:23:34,400 --> 00:23:36,320
And I was always wrong.
而且我總是錯的

319
00:23:39,360 --> 00:23:42,000
I've had relationships I really didn't want at all.
我有談過戀愛  但我真的根本不想談

320
00:23:42,080 --> 00:23:44,560
I've had friends that I never liked.
我有一些我從未喜歡過的朋友

321
00:23:45,360 --> 00:23:48,120
I couldn't say no to anyone.
我不能拒絕任何人

322
00:23:49,600 --> 00:23:50,760
I don't know why,
我不知道為什麼

323
00:23:50,840 --> 00:23:54,120
but I always cared so much about what people thought about me.
但我總是非常關心人們對我的看法

324
00:23:55,600 --> 00:23:58,360
As thought I had to make everyone happy.
以為我不得不讓每個人都開心

325
00:24:00,280 --> 00:24:01,360
Because...
因為

326
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:03,920
You're...
你是

327
00:24:05,240 --> 00:24:06,240
Good.
好人

328
00:24:08,000 --> 00:24:09,120
No.
不是

